<div id="review_34269672" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/34269672" />
    <a title="Elizabeth" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/522123-elizabeth"><img alt="Elizabeth" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1201094337p2/522123.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/34269672?book_show_action=true">Oct 01, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Elizabeth" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Elizabeth" href="/user/show/522123-elizabeth">Elizabeth</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>


          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">anyone who wants to be a bread expert, but has energy to invest in the efforts</span></div>

        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer34269672" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2224726298484167139">I checked this book out from the library because I just learned to bake a couple types of bread, and I wanted to be a bread expert. This book, if you read it and take it seriously, WILL make you a bread baking expert. I didn&apos;t realize until I spent about 30 minutes with this book that I have no interest in exerting the time and energy it takes to BECOME a bread expert....so it wasn&apos;t entirely what I was looking for. Maybe I need a book about how to fake being an expert baker without exerting the</span>
  <span id="freeText2224726298484167139" style="display:none">I checked this book out from the library because I just learned to bake a couple types of bread, and I wanted to be a bread expert. This book, if you read it and take it seriously, WILL make you a bread baking expert. I didn't realize until I spent about 30 minutes with this book that I have no interest in exerting the time and energy it takes to BECOME a bread expert....so it wasn't entirely what I was looking for. Maybe I need a book about how to fake being an expert baker without exerting the energy. For now, if I want fine artisan breads, I'll let the bakery do the work.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2224726298484167139" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
