<span id="freeTextContainer7123588826179420511">Fantastic bread-baking bible, but as per her usual, RLB is insanely nitpicky on some things that probably don&apos;t need to be so nitpicky. On the other hand, sometimes if you go off-piste with this book, you end up with a cracker :D Not for the faint of heart or the early-days bread baker, it can be daunting and frustrating to deal with a recipe with three proofings (proves? proofs?) after making a sponge/biga. Some of the results are absolutely spectacular, but there are times when you just don&apos;t </span>
  <span id="freeText7123588826179420511" style="display:none">Fantastic bread-baking bible, but as per her usual, RLB is insanely nitpicky on some things that probably don't need to be so nitpicky. On the other hand, sometimes if you go off-piste with this book, you end up with a cracker :D Not for the faint of heart or the early-days bread baker, it can be daunting and frustrating to deal with a recipe with three proofings (proves? proofs?) after making a sponge/biga. Some of the results are absolutely spectacular, but there are times when you just don't have the energy to spend your ENTIRE DAY coming up with one pretty-unspectacular appearing loaf (one of my favorites recipes herein is just that, looks completely blah, but the taste is just incredible). </span>
